import com.google.gson.Gson
import groovy.json.JsonSlurper

def jsonSlurper = new JsonSlurper();

//result map do not remove
result = [:]

ctx = jsonSlurper.parseText(context)
data_inputparams = jsonSlurper.parseText(inputParameter)
data_httpbody = getValues(data_inputparams.getAt("contractDetails"),jsonSlurper)
data_outputparams = jsonSlurper.parseText(outputParameters)

def getValues(List list,JsonSlurper jsonSlurper){
    paramValuesList = []
    for(Map map:list) {
        map.each {
            key,value ->
                for(String valueList:((ArrayList)jsonSlurper.parseText(value))){
                    paramValuesList.add(valueList)
                }
        }
    }
    return paramValuesList
}


def createResultParameter(String subjectIri, HashMap<String, String> keyValue) {
    resultValue = [:]
    keyValue.each { key, value ->
        resultValue.put(key, value)
    }
    result.put(subjectIri, resultValue)
}

//Main function
def main(JsonSlurper jsonSlurper) {
    Gson gson = new Gson();
    mapGraph = [:]
    httpBody = ""
    resultList = []
    Dataset ds = DatasetFactory.createTxnMem() ;
    for(String res:data_httpbody) {
        mapGraph["@context"] = ctx
        paramValuesList = []
        paramValuesList.add(jsonSlurper.parseText(res))
        mapGraph["@graph"] = paramValuesList
        resultString = gson.toJson(mapGraph, Map.class);
        InputStream is = IOUtils.toInputStream(resultString, "UTF-8");
        RDFParser.source(is).lang(RDFLanguages.JSONLD)
                .parse(ds);
        qry = "PREFIX part: <http://kg.scania.com/part#>\n" +
                "PREFIX contract: <http://kg.scania.com/contract#>\n" +
                "PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>\n" +
                "PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>\n" +
                "PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>\n" +
                "PREFIX unit: <http://qudt.org/vocab/unit/>\n" +
                "PREFIX skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#>\n" +
                "PREFIX time: <https://www.w3.org/TR/owl-time/#>\n" +
                "\n" +
                "CONSTRUCT {\n" +
                "?part_iri part:hasContract ?contract_iri ;\n" +
                "          part:partNumber ?part_number ;\n" +
                "          part:hasPartFamily ?part_family_iri .\n" +
                "\n" +
                "?part_family_iri a part:PartFamily ;\n" +
                "      rdfs:label ?part_family .\n" +
                "\n" +
                "?contract_iri rdf:type contract:Contract ;\n" +
                "              contract:contractNumber ?contract_no ;\n" +
                "              contract:totalPrice ?price ;\n" +
                "              contract:validFrom ?valid_from ;\n" +
                "              contract:consistsOfPart ?part_iri ;\n" +
                "              part:materialGroup ?material_group ;\n" +
                "              part:hasSourcingArea ?sourcingArea ;\n" +
                "              contract:currency ?currency ;\n" +
                "              contract:hasPurchaser ?purchaser_iri ;\n" +
                "              contract:hasSupplier ?supplier_iri ;\n" +
                "            .\n" +
                "\n" +
                "?purchaser_iri a contract:Purchaser ;\n" +
                "                 contract:belongsToSourcingArea ?sourcingArea ;\n" +
                "                 contract:purchaserCode ?purchaser_code .\n" +
                "\n" +
                "?supplier_iri a contract:Supplier ;\n" +
                "                contract:supplierNumber ?supplier_number ;\n" +
                "                contract:supplierName ?supplier_name .\n" +
                "}\n" +
                "\n" +
                "WHERE{\n" +
                "    # scope to the results from the api response\n" +
                "    ?sub part:data [part:result ?contract] .\n" +
                "\n" +
                "      # CONTRACT\n" +
                "      # fetch contract number/ID from api response\n" +
                "      ?contract part:ContractNo ?contract_no .\n" +
                "\n" +
                "      # fetch price from api response\n" +
                "      OPTIONAL {?contract part:price ?price_E ;\n" +
                "                          part:Currency ?currency .\n" +
                "                # resolve e-notation of the float\n" +
                "                BIND(strafter(str(?price_E), \"E\") as ?E)\n" +
                "                BIND(replace(strbefore(str(?price_E), \"E\"), \"[.]\", \"\") as ?nodot)\n" +
                "                BIND( substr(?nodot, 0, xsd:integer(?E)+2) as ?first)\n" +
                "                BIND(substr(?nodot, xsd:integer(?E)+2, 2) as ?second)\n" +
                "                BIND(concat(?first, \".\", ?second) as ?price)\n" +
                "                }\n" +
                "\n" +
                "      # fetch 'valid from' date from api response\n" +
                "      OPTIONAL {?contract part:ValidFrom ?valid_from_input .\n" +
                "                # set date in the correct format (xsd:dateTime)\n" +
                "                BIND(substr(str(?valid_from_input), 1,2) as ?dd)\n" +
                "                BIND(substr(str(?valid_from_input), 4,2) as ?mm)\n" +
                "                BIND(substr(str(?valid_from_input), 7,4) as ?YYYY)\n" +
                "                BIND(STRDT(STR(concat(?YYYY,\"-\", ?mm, '-', ?dd, 'T00:00:00')), xsd:dateTime) as ?valid_from)\n" +
                "                }\n" +
                "\n" +
                "      # SUPPLIER\n" +
                "      # fetch supplier number/ID from api response\n" +
                "      OPTIONAL {?contract part:SupplierNumber ?supplier_number .\n" +
                "                # bind supplier number to generate supplier individual\n" +
                "                BIND(URI(CONCAT(\"http://kg.scania.com/contract#Supplier_\", str(?supplier_number))) as ?supplier_iri)}\n" +
                "      \n" +
                "      # fetch supplier name from api response\n" +
                "      OPTIONAL {?contract part:SupplierName ?supplier_name .}\n" +
                "\n" +
                "      # fetch unit from api response\n" +
                "      OPTIONAL {?contract part:Unit ?unit .}\n" +
                "\n" +
                "      # PURCHASER\n" +
                "      # fetch purchaser code from api response\n" +
                "      OPTIONAL {?contract part:PurchaserCode ?purchaser_code .\n" +
                "                # bind purchaser code to generate purchaser individual\n" +
                "                BIND(URI(CONCAT(\"http://kg.scania.com/contract#Purchaser_\", str(?purchaser_code))) as ?purchaser_iri)}\n" +
                "      \n" +
                "      # fetch sourcing area from api response\n" +
                "      OPTIONAL {?contract part:SourcingArea ?sourcingArea_str .\n" +
                "                # sourcing areas are individuals in the ontology, therfore need the iri to refer to them\n" +
                "                BIND(URI(CONCAT(\"http://kg.scania.com/contract#SourcingArea_\", str(?sourcingArea_str))) as ?sourcingArea)}\n" +
                "\n" +
                "      # PART\n" +
                "      # fetch part number from api response\n" +
                "      OPTIONAL {?contract part:PartNumber ?part_number .}\n" +
                "     \n" +
                "      # fetch material group from api response\n" +
                "      OPTIONAL {?contract part:MaterialGroup ?material_group .}\n" +
                "      \n" +
                "      # fetch part family from api response\n" +
                "      OPTIONAL {?contract part:PartFamily ?part_family_str .\n" +
                "               # bind part family name/code to generate part family individual with rdfs:label\n" +
                "               BIND(strlang(str(?part_family_str), \"en\") as ?part_family)\n" +
                "               BIND(URI(CONCAT(\"http://kg.scania.com/part#PartFamily_\", str(?part_family_str))) as ?part_family_iri)}\n" +
                "\n" +
                "    # Create contract and part individuals based on their respective IDs\n" +
                "    BIND(URI(CONCAT(\"http://kg.scania.com/contract#Contract_\", str(?contract_no))) as ?contract_iri)\n" +
                "    BIND(URI(CONCAT(\"http://kg.scania.com/part#Part_\", str(?part_number))) as ?part_iri)\n" +
                "}\n";

        Query query = QueryFactory.create(qry);
        ds.begin(ReadWrite.READ);
        try {
            QueryExecution qexec = QueryExecutionFactory.create(query, ds);
            Model modelresult = qexec.execConstruct();
            StringWriter out = new StringWriter();
            RDFDataMgr.write(out, modelresult, Lang.JSONLD);
            httpBody = out.toString();
            //System.out.println(out.toString());
            qexec.close();
        } finally {
            ds.end();
        }
		
        resultList.add(httpBody)
        resultmap = [:]
        resultmap.put("httpBody", resultList)

        createResultParameter(data_outputparams.get("param_contractDetails_stardog"), resultmap)
    }
}

main(jsonSlurper)
return result

//Main function
def main(JsonSlurper jsonSlurper) {
    Gson gson = new Gson();
    mapGraph = [:]
    httpBody = ""
    resultList = []
    Dataset ds = DatasetFactory.createTxnMem();
    for (String res : data_httpbody) {
        mapGraph["@context"] = ctx
        paramValuesList = []
        paramValuesList.add(jsonSlurper.parseText(res))
        mapGraph["@graph"] = paramValuesList
        resultString = gson.toJson(mapGraph, Map.class);
        InputStream is = IOUtils.toInputStream(resultString, "UTF-8");
        RDFParser.source(is).lang(RDFLanguages.JSONLD)
                .parse(ds);
        qry = "PREFIX : <http://kg.scania.com/part#>\n" +
                "PREFIX contract: <http://kg.scania.com/contract#>\n" +
                "PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>\n" +
                "PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>\n" +
                "PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>\n" +
                "PREFIX unit: <http://qudt.org/vocab/unit/>\n" +
                "PREFIX skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#>\n" +
                "PREFIX time: <https://www.w3.org/TR/owl-time/#>\n" +
                "\n" +
                "CONSTRUCT{\n" +
                "    ?part :partNumber ?part_value ;\n" +
                "          rdfs:label ?partLabel ;\n" +
                "          rdf:type :Part ;\n" +
                "          :hasSourcingArea ?sourcingArea ;\n" +
                "          :purchasedBy ?purchaser_iri ;\n" +
                "          :hasUnitOfMeasure ?UOM_value ;\n" +
                "          :nameLong ?nameLong ;\n" +
                "          :hasStatus ?partStatus ;\n" +
                "          :byDesignGroup ?DesignGroup ;\n" +
                "          :nameShort ?nameShort ;\n" +
                "          :hasIntroCO ?introCO ;\n" +
                "          :designerResponsible ?designResponsible ;\n" +
                "          :hasDefiningDocument [contract:hasDrawingFromOAS ?drawing] ;\n" +
                "          :hasLastCO ?lastCO ;\n" +
                "          :toBeImplemented ?toBeImplemented ;\n" +
                "          :estimatedWeight ?weight ;\n" +
                "          :hasDiscontinuedSparePartCode ?dspCode ;\n" +
                "          :hasMaterial ?material .\n" +
                "\n" +
                "?purchaser_iri a contract:Purchaser ;\n" +
                "                 contract:purchaserCode ?purchaserCode ;\n" +
                "                 contract:belongsToSourcingArea ?sourcingArea_pur .\n" +
                "\n" +
                "}\n" +
                "WHERE {            \n" +
                "      ?sub  :alias \"part\" ;\n" +
                "            :values ?partvalue ;\n" +
                "            :objects ?obj ;\n" +
                "            :displaytypename ?sub_label ;\n" +
                "            :displaytypenamelang ?sub_lang .\n" +
                "      \n" +
                "      ?partvalue :value ?part_value_int .\n" +
                "                  \n" +
                "      # bind values from the source to expected data type and composition\n" +
                "      BIND(str(?part_value_int) as ?part_value)\n" +
                "      BIND(URI(CONCAT(\"http://kg.scania.com/part#Part_\",str(?part_value))) as ?part)\n" +
                "      BIND(strlang(str(?sub_label), str(?sub_lang)) as ?partLabel)\n" +
                "      \n" +
                "      # fetch unit of measure from source data\n" +
                "      OPTIONAL{?obj_uom  :type \"unit_of_measure\" ;\n" +
                "                     :objects ?obj1_uom .\n" +
                "               ?obj1_uom  :type \"item_name_long\" ;\n" +
                "                     :values ?values_uom .\n" +
                "\n" +
                "               ?values_uom :value ?UOM_value_wo_lang ; :lang ?uom_lang .\n" +
                "               # bind language to the unit of measure value\n" +
                "               BIND(strlang(str(?UOM_value_wo_lang), str(?uom_lang)) as ?UOM_value)}\n" +
                "\n" +
                "      # fetch part name (long) from source data\n" +
                "      OPTIONAL{?obj :type \"item_name_long\" ;\n" +
                "                     :displaytypenamelang ?namelong_lang ;\n" +
                "                     :values ?values_namelong .\n" +
                "               ?values_namelong :value ?nameLong_wo_lang .\n" +
                "               # bind language to part name (long)\n" +
                "               BIND(strlang(str(?nameLong_wo_lang), str(?namelong_lang)) as ?nameLong)}\n" +
                "\n" +
                "      # fetch part status code from source data\n" +
                "      OPTIONAL{?obj_status :type \"part_status\" ;\n" +
                "                     :values ?values_status .\n" +
                "               ?values_status :value ?partStatus_str .\n" +
                "               # Part status are individuals in the ontology, need to refer to the respective IRI\n" +
                "               BIND(URI(CONCAT(\"http://kg.scania.com/part#Status\",str(?partStatus_str))) as ?partStatus)}\n" +
                "\n" +
                "      # fetch design group from source data\n" +
                "      OPTIONAL{?obj_designgroup :type \"designgroup\" ;\n" +
                "                     :values ?values_designgroup .\n" +
                "               ?values_designgroup :value ?DesignGroup.}\n" +
                "\n" +
                "      # fetch part name (short) from source data\n" +
                "      OPTIONAL{?obj_nameshort :type \"item_name_short\" ;\n" +
                "                     :displaytypenamelang ?lang ;\n" +
                "                     :values ?values_nameshort .\n" +
                "               ?values_nameshort :value ?nameShort_wo_lang .\n" +
                "               # bind language to part name (short)\n" +
                "               BIND(strlang(str(?nameShort_wo_lang), str(?lang)) as ?nameShort)}\n" +
                "\n" +
                "      # fetch intro CO from source data\n" +
                "      OPTIONAL{?obj_introco :type \"intro_co\" ;\n" +
                "                     :values ?values_introco .\n" +
                "               ?values_introco :value ?introCO .}\n" +
                "\n" +
                "      # fetch name of designer responsible from source data (misspelled)\n" +
                "      OPTIONAL{?obj_designresp :type \"design_responsibl\" ;\n" +
                "                     :values ?values_designresp .\n" +
                "               ?values_designresp :value ?designResponsible .}\n" +
                "\n" +
                "      # fetch name of designer responsible from source data\n" +
                "      OPTIONAL{?obj_designresp :displaytypename \"Design Responsible\" ;\n" +
                "                     :values ?values_designresp .\n" +
                "               ?values_designresp :value ?designResponsible .}\n" +
                "\n" +
                "      # fetch defining document (drawing ID) from source data\n" +
                "      OPTIONAL{?obj_defdocument :type \"defining_document\" ;\n" +
                "                     :relation ?relation_defdocument .\n" +
                "               ?relation_defdocument :objects ?obj1_defdocument .\n" +
                "               ?obj1_defdocument :type \"drawing\" ;\n" +
                "                     :values ?values_defdocument .\n" +
                "               ?values_defdocument :value ?drawing .}\n" +
                "\n" +
                "      # fetch last CO from source data\n" +
                "      OPTIONAL{?obj_lastco :type \"last_co\" ;\n" +
                "                     :values ?values_lastco .\n" +
                "               ?values_lastco  :value ?lastCO .}\n" +
                "\n" +
                "      # fetch placeholder for data from data source\n" +
                "      OPTIONAL{?obj_tbi :type \"tobeimplemented\" ;\n" +
                "                     :values ?values_tbi .\n" +
                "               ?values_tbi :value ?toBeImplemented .}\n" +
                "\n" +
                "      # fetch estimated weight from source data\n" +
                "      OPTIONAL{?obj_estweight :type \"estimated_weight\" ;\n" +
                "                     :values ?values_estweight .\n" +
                "               ?values_estweight :value ?weight_wo_unit .\n" +
                "               # bind data type float to weight\n" +
                "               BIND(xsd:float(?weight_wo_unit) as ?weight)}\n" +
                "\n" +
                "      # fetch material from source data\n" +
                "      OPTIONAL{?obj_material :type \"material\" ;\n" +
                "                     :values ?values_material .\n" +
                "               ?values_material :value ?material .\n" +
                "                     }\n" +
                "\n" +
                "      # fetch sourcing area from source data\n" +
                "      OPTIONAL{?obj_sourcingarea :type \"sourcing_area\" ;\n" +
                "                     :values ?values_sourcingarea .\n" +
                "               ?values_sourcingarea :value ?sourcingArea_str .\n" +
                "               # Sourcing Areas are individuals in the ontology, need to refer to the respective IRI\n" +
                "               BIND(URI(CONCAT(\"http://kg.scania.com/contract#SourcingArea_\", str(?sourcingArea_str))) as ?sourcingArea)}\n" +
                "                  \n" +
                "      # fetch sourcing area and respectiive purchaser from source data\n" +
                "      OPTIONAL{?obj_sourcingarea :type \"sourcing_area\" ;\n" +
                "                     :values ?values_sourcingarea .\n" +
                "               ?values_sourcingarea :value ?sourcingArea_pur_str .\n" +
                "               # Sourcing Areas are individuals in the ontology, need to refer to the respective IRI\n" +
                "               BIND(URI(CONCAT(\"http://kg.scania.com/contract#SourcingArea_\", str(?sourcingArea_pur_str))) as ?sourcingArea_pur)\n" +
                "                              \n" +
                "               # fetch purchaser belonging to the sourcing area\n" +
                "               ?obj_sourcingarea :relation [:objects ?obj_purchasercode] .\n" +
                "               ?obj_purchasercode :type \"purchaser_code\" ;\n" +
                "                     :values ?values_purchasercode .\n" +
                "               ?values_purchasercode :value ?purchaserCode .\n" +
                "               # Purchaser sholud be an individual with proper IRI\n" +
                "               BIND(URI(CONCAT(\"http://kg.scania.com/contract#Purchaser_\", str(?purchaserCode))) as ?purchaser_iri)}\n" +
                "\n" +
                "      # fetch discontinued spare part code from source data\n" +
                "      {OPTIONAL{?obj_dsp :type \"discontinued_spare_part_code\" ;\n" +
                "                     :values ?values_dsp .\n" +
                "               ?values_dsp :value ?dspCode_str .\n" +
                "               # Discontinued SPare Part Codes are individuals in the ontology, need to refer to the respective IRI\n" +
                "               BIND(URI(CONCAT(\"http://kg.scania.com/part#DSPC\",str(?dspCode_str))) as ?dspCode)}}\n" +
                "   }\n";
        Query query = QueryFactory.create(qry);
        ds.begin(ReadWrite.READ);
        try {
            QueryExecution qexec = QueryExecutionFactory.create(query, ds);
            Model modelresult = qexec.execConstruct();
            StringWriter out = new StringWriter();
            RDFDataMgr.write(out, modelresult, Lang.JSONLD);
            httpBody = out.toString();
            //System.out.println(out.toString());
            qexec.close();
        } finally {
            ds.end();
        }
        resultList.add(httpBody)
        resultmap = [:]
        resultmap.put("httpBody", resultList)
        createResultParameter(data_outputparams.get("param_partDetails_stardog"), resultmap)

    }
}

main(jsonSlurper)
setPartDetails(jsonSlurper)
return result
